{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μνήμ-η</b>, <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>μνάμα</b>, ἡ, (μνάομαι) <b>remembrance, memory</b> of a person or thing, <i>absolutely</i> or with <i>genitive</i>, κακῶν μ. γίνεται οὐδεμία [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 798; οὔτ᾽ ἀγαθῶν μνήμην εἰδότες οὔτε κακῶν [prev. author] 1114; τῶν ἐμῶν μνάμα ποκ᾽ ἐσσεῖται πόνων 5th c.BC: Epicharmus Comicus 254 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; λείπεσθαι ἀθάνατον μ. (i.e. ἑαυτοῦ) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.144; μ. ἔχειν τινός 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1246, “OC” 509, etc.; τάφου μ. τίθεσθαι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 1585 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ ἄνθρωποι πρὸς ἃ ἔπασχον τὴν μ. ἐποιοῦντο made their <b>recollections</b> suit their sufferings, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.54 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μνήμην πεποίηκεν has made [him] <b>remembered</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1414a6: _plural_, ἀγήρατοι μνῆμαι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.79 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the dead, μακαρίας μνήμης, θείας μνήμης, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.175 (from Megara), 6th c.AD: Justinianus Imperator “Novellae” 43 “Praef.”, etc.\">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]; κρατίστης μνήμης Wilcken [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Chr.” 26.30 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; μνήμης ἀρίστης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.2808.6 (Hyettus, 3rd c.AD). \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>memory</b> as a power of the mind, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 146, etc.; μνήμην ἁπάντων μουσομήτορ᾽ ἐργάνην 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 461 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; proper to animals, opposed to ἀνάμνησις, of man, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 34c, compare μνημονεύω 1.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἰπεῖν τι μνήμης ἄπο from <b>memory</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1131; ἐν μνήμῃ λαβεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 26b; φυλάξαι τῇ μ. [prev. author] “Lg.” 783c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς μ. ἀναληπτέον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 864b; ἐφ᾽ ὅσον μ. ἀνθρώπων ἐφικνεῖται 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.5.8; φέρειν ἐν μ. 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Μονόστιχοι - Fragmenta Comicorum Graecorum” 435: _plural_, αἱ πολλαὶ μ. τοῦ αὐτοῦ πράγματος μιᾶς ἐμπειρίας δύναμιν ἀποτελοῦσιν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] all the <b>memories, acts of memory</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 980b29, compare “APo.” 100a5 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>powers of memory</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Rh.” 1362b24 (assuming variant). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>memorial, record</b>, κυπαρίττιναι μνῆμαι εἰς τὸν ἔπειτα χρόνον καταγεγραμμέναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 741c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μνῆμαι ἐν μέτροις καὶ ἄνευ μέτρων <b>inscriptions</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1361a34 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; μ. μυθολόγος mythological <b>record, history</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Aetia” 3.1.55, compare 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “περὶ αἱρέσεων τοῖς εἰσαγομένοις” 2. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>mention, notice</b> of a thing, μ. ποιεῖσθαί τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.15, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μ. ποιήσασθαι περί or ὑπέρ τινος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 2.7.12, 2.71.1; ἡ ὑπὲρ τῶν δικαίων μ. 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 15.52; μ. ἔχειν τινός 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.14, etc. (compare above 1); μ. ἐπασκέειν [prev. author] 2.77. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> μνήμη βασίλειος the imperial <b>cabinet</b> or <b>archives</b>, τῆς β. μ. προεστώς, = Latin <i>a memoria</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 4.8.4, compare 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 76.14 (probably). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> ={μνῆμα}, <b>tomb</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “AJP” 48.18 (from Rome). \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G3420","accentedUnicode":"μνήμη","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3403","matchingForm":"μιμνήσκω","stepTransliteration":"mimnēskō","gloss":"to remember","_zh_tw_Gloss":"要記念","_es_Gloss":"recordar","_zh_Gloss":"要记念"},{"strongNumber":"G3419","matchingForm":"μνημεῖον","stepTransliteration":"mnēmeion","gloss":"grave","_zh_tw_Gloss":"墳墓","_es_Gloss":"tumba","_zh_Gloss":"坟墓"},{"strongNumber":"G3421","matchingForm":"μνημονεύω","stepTransliteration":"mnēmoneuō","gloss":"to remember","_zh_tw_Gloss":"記念","_es_Gloss":"recordar","_zh_Gloss":"记念"}],"shortDef":"remembrance, recalling, memory","mediumDef":"remembrance, recalling, memory <br /><b>remembrance, recollection, memory;</b>, <greek>μνήμην ποιεισθαι</greek>, <b>to make mention,</b> <ref='2Pe.1.15'>2Pet. 1:15</ref>*","stepGloss":"remembrance","stepTransliteration":"mnēmē","count":1,"_es_Definition":"recuerdo, memoria","_zh_tw_Definition":"回想, 回憶 (彼後 1:15)","_zh_Definition":"回想, 回忆 (彼后 1:15)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự nhớ lại; sự nhớ đến","_zh_tw_Gloss":"記念","_es_Gloss":"memoria","_zh_Gloss":"记念"}]}